  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/dealfluence--adeu",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Adeu: Native Track Changes for AI",
    "description": "Agentic DOCX Redlining Engine. Enables LLMs to read Word documents and inject native Track Changes (w:ins, w:del) and Comments without breaking formatting. Includes Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-11T04:20:08.457Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11T04:20:08.457Z",
    "keywords": [
      "agentic-ai",
      "docx",
      "legal-tech",
      "llm",
      "mcp",
      "python",
      "redlining",
      "track-changes",
      "word-processing"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "**Adeu bridges the gap between LLM text generation and Microsoft Word.**",
    "context": "**Adeu bridges the gap between LLM text generation and Microsoft Word.**\n\nLLMs speak Markdown; Lawyers speak \"Track Changes.\" Adeu allows AI agents to propose edits to `.docx` files without breaking formatting, numbering, or complex layouts.\n\nIt treats the DOCX file as a **Virtual DOM**:\n1.  **Ingest:** Extracts a lightweight, token-efficient text representation for the AI.\n2.  **Diff:** Calculates changes based on the AI's edits.\n3.  **Reconcile:** Surgically injects native XML `w:ins` (insertions) and `w:del` (deletions) back into the original document.\n\n---",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
  "domains": [
    "machine-learning",
    "lang:python"
  ],
